<paragraph pageId="17" pageNumber="48" type="mainText">Epigyne (Figs. 21, 22, 25, cleared Fig. 31). Opening of median cavity narrow, most of it covered by a median septum. Each side with lateral elevation extending into a more or less triangle-shaped sclerite covering the receptacle. Bottom of median cavity corrugated, with characteristic shape in dorsal view (Fig. 22).</paragraph>
